<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="133" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,906,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1050,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is the only one found in 
<collectingCountry box="[753,818,1050,1076]" name="Libya" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Libya</collectingCountry>
and currently can be considered endemic to the country. A morphometric analyses showed no clear separation of the species towards the other members of the genus (for details see Dey et al. accepted). Morphologically the species is somehow similar to the species from the Atlas Mountains, but differs in the strong pubescence of the body, the comparably slender hind femora and the orangered base of the hind wings, as well as the hind wing band not reaching the upper margins of the wing (
<figureCitation box="[1297,1424,1194,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[235,1351,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2: Variation in wing morphology of male and female individuals of the valid members of the genus Thalpomena: A—Thalpomena algeriana; B—Thalpomena azureipennis; C—Thalpomena coerulescens; D—Thalpomena dernensis and E—Thalpomena viridipennis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6127872/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Figure 2 D</figureCitation>
). Interestingly, molecular data of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Salfi" authorityYear="1927" box="[508,763,1230,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Thalpomena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dernensis">
<emphasis box="[508,763,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Thalpomena dernensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show a clear clustering with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dey et al., 2022)" baseAuthorityName="Dey" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Thalpomena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridipennis">
<emphasis box="[1092,1373,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Thalpomena viridipennis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dey, L. - S. &amp; Hochkirch, A. &amp; Moussi, A. &amp; Simoes, M. V. P. &amp; Husemann, M." pageId="4" pageNumber="133" refId="ref4932" refString="Dey, L. - S., Hochkirch, A., Moussi, A., Simoes, M. V. P. &amp; Husemann, M. (2022) Diversification in and around the Atlas Mountains: insights into the systematics and biogeography of the genus Thalpomena (Orthoptera: Acrididae: Oedipodinae). Sytematic Entomology. [early view] https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12537" type="book" year="2022">Dey et al., 2022</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Further sampling is needed to clarify the status of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
